The number of deaths in China’s central Hubei province from a coronavirus outbreak had risen by 81 to 699 as of Friday, the province’s health commission said in a statement on its website on Saturday. There had been a further 2 841 cases detected in Hubei, the epicenter of the outbreak, taking the total in the province to 24 953. Most of the new deaths were in Hubei’s provincial capital of Wuhan, where the virus is believed to have originated. Wuhan reported 67 new deaths on Friday, up from 64 on Thursday. A total of 545 people in Wuhan have now died from the virus. New confirmed cases in Wuhan increased by 1 985 on Friday, up from 1 501 on Thursday.